1.3 URLify

Write a method to replace all spaces in a string with '%20'. 
You may assume that the string has sufficient space at the end to hold the additional characters, and that you are given the "true" length of the string.
(Note: If implementing in Java, please use a character array so that you can perform this operation in place.)

Input: ['s', 'a', 'm', 'i', ' ', '.', ' ', 'c', 'o', 'm', '', '', '', '', '', ''], 10
Output: ['s', 'a', 'm', 'i', '%', '2', '0', '.', '%', '2', '0', 'c', 'o', 'm']

If we didn't have to do this in place, it would be simple:
	loop through array, and add chars to a new array
	when you see a white space, add '%20' in the new array
	repeat till end of string

If we do this in place, we need to first find the number of empty spaces in the string.
This will help figure out what index we need to start on (since we do not know the actual length of the array)

Take a look at the following example:
Input: ['s', 'a', 'm', 'i', ' ', '.', ' ', 'c', 'o', 'm', '', '', '', '', '', ''], 10
	We need to start at index 13 (because we are removing 1 char (empty space) and adding 3 chars)
	Since the string ends at index 9 (trueIdx), we can start from index 13 (idx) and move backwards from both index 9 and 13.
	We continously swap the characters at both positions.
	If we see a ' ', we add '%', '2', '0' and decrement idx by 3
	
												trueidx			  idx
	['s', 'a', 'm', 'i', ' ', '.', ' ', 'c', 'o', 'm', '', '', '', '', '', '']
	
								  trueidx			   idx
	['s', 'a', 'm', 'i', ' ', '.', ' ', 'c', 'o', 'm', '', 'c', 'o', 'm', '', '']
	
							trueidx	 	idx
	['s', 'a', 'm', 'i', ' ', '.', ' ', 'c', '%', '2', '0', 'c', 'o', 'm', '', '']
	
						trueidx	   idx
	['s', 'a', 'm', 'i', ' ', '.', ' ', '.', '%', '2', '0', 'c', 'o', 'm', '', '']
						  idx
						trueidx	   
	['s', 'a', 'm', 'i', '%', '2', '0', '.', '%', '2', '0', 'c', 'o', 'm', '', '']

	idx
	trueidx	   
	['s', 'a', 'm', 'i', '%', '2', '0', '.', '%', '2', '0', 'c', 'o', 'm', '', '']
	
This Algo takes us O(n) time since we loop through the array once and O(1) space as we did it in-place.

public static void urlify(char[] url, int trueLength) {

	// find number of spaces in the original string
	int spaces = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i < trueLength;  i++) {
		if (url[i] == ' ' ) {
			spaces++;
		}
	}
	
	if (spaces == 0) {
		return;
	}
	
	int idx = trueLength - 1  + spaces * 2;
	for (int trueIdx = trueLength - 1; trueIdx >= 0; trueIdx--)  {
		if (url[trueIdx] == ' ') {
			url[idx] = '0';
			url[idx - 1] = '2';
			url[idx - 2] = '%';
			idx = idx - 3;
		} else {
			url[idx] = url[trueIdx];
			idx--;
		}
	}	
}

